(15, 'Dr.Prabhakar S. Kedar', 'Haematogenetics', 'Scientist E', 'prabhakar-kedar-1543404016-1.jpg', 'kedarps2002@yahoo.com', '+( 91-22) 2413 8518/19 /; Extn : 734', '022 24138521', '<ul class=\"style110\">\r\n	<li><strong>MSc </strong> Nagpur University, Maharashtra (Biochemistry ; 1992)</li>\r\n	<li><strong>PhD </strong>Kyushu Institute of Technology, Fukuoka, JAPAN (Under DST-JSPS Ronpaku Fellowship Program)(Biotechnology/ Biomedical Engineering; 2007)</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Post Doc </strong> BIDMC, Harvard Medical School, Boston MA USA (Red cell membrane protein defects; 2010)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<ul class=\"style110\">\r\n	<li class=\"style109\">Life member of Indian Society of Human Genetics.(ISHG)</li>\r\n	<li class=\"style109\">Life member of Mumbai Hematology Group. (MHG)</li>\r\n	<li class=\"style109\">Life member of Indian Society of Hematology and Transfusion Medicine. (ISHTM)</li>\r\n	<li class=\"style109\">Life members of Association for the Promotion of DNA fingerprinting and other DNA technologies,(ADNAT)</li>\r\n	<li>Life member of Indian JSPS Alumni Association (IJAA). Tokyo, Japan</li>\r\n	<li>Life member of Molecular Pathology Association of India, Mumbai.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<ul class=\"style110\">\r\n	<li>Red cell enzymopathies</li>\r\n	<li>Red cell membrane protein disorder</li>\r\n	<li>Hemoglobinopathies</li>\r\n	<li>Congenital Methemoglobinemia</li>\r\n	<li>Congenital dyserythropoietic anemia</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<h4>Foreign Visits</h4>\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"style110\">\r\n	<li>Awarded ICMR Prize for Biomedical Research for Scientists Belonging to Underprivileged Communities for the year 2013 by Honorable Health Minister Shri Jagat Prasad Nadda at Auditorium of National Academy of Medical Sciences ( India), Ansari Nagar, New Delhi on October 11, 2017.</li>\r\n	<li>Awarded ICMR International fellowship for Senior Scientist -2016 program (15 Days) at WIMS, University of Oxford. Oxford (UK).</li>\r\n	<li>Awarded ICMR International fellowship for Young Biomedical Scientist -2010. (Period 1st February 2010 to 31st August 2010: Six Months at Harvard Medical School Boston, USA.)</li>\r\n	<li>American Society of Hematology (ASH) Meeting (USA) sponsorship Award by Mumbai Hematology group for best research paper presented at Annual Conference of Mumbai Hematology Group at Tata Memorial Hospital. Mumbai on 8th to 16th Oct 2007.</li>\r\n	<li>Ronpaku Gold Medal for PhD Thesis awarded by Japan Society of Promotion of science, Tokyo under DST-JSPS RONPAKU Fellowship-2004.</li>\r\n	<li>Department of Science and Technology (DST) New Delhi awarded JSPS (RONPAKU) fellowship for Doctor of Philosophy (PhD) from Japan in the year 2003.</li>\r\n	<li>J C Patel Award for best research Paper entitled &ldquo;Eosin 5&rsquo; maleimide as a diagnostic tool for Red cell membrane cytoskeleton Disorders&rdquo;: presented at Annual Conference of Bombay Hematology Group at Tata Memorial Hospital. Mumbai, 15th to 16th Feb 2003.</li>\r\n	<li>Awarded Hindi Diploma in First Division with distinction conducted by Central Hindi Directorate. New Delhi (1995).</li>\r\n	<li>Worked under PhD Japanese Advisor Prof. Kazuyuki Shimizu, Dept. of Bioscience and Bioinformatics, Kyushu Institute of Technology, Fukuoka ,Japan for three months every year from 200 4 to 2008 under DST JSPS Ronpaku PhD Program. 15 April to 14th July 2004; 1st May to 30th August 2005; 1st April to 30th June 2006</li>\r\n	<li>Worked under Japanese PhD co-guide Prof Hotoshi Kanno, Department of Advance Biomedical Engineering and Sciences, Tokyo Women Medical University, Tokyo, Japan for one month every year from 2004 to 2008 under DST JSPS Ronpaku Program.(period: 1st May to 30 May 2004, 1st May to 30th May 2005; 1st May to 30th May 2006;)</li>\r\n	<li>Participated and presented paper in the 49th Annual meeting of American Society of Hematology (ASH) held at the Georgia World Congress Center in Atlanta, Georgia, USA, period 6-11th December 2007.</li>\r\n	<li>Worked Under Prof. Seth Alper, Department of Medicine, Beth Israel Deaconess Medical Center East Campus, Harvard Medical School, Boston, MA (USA) from 1st February to 31st July 2010 ( Six months) under ICMR International fellowship for Indian Young Biomedical Scientist 2009-2010</li>\r\n	<li>Under Prof. D.R. Higgs FRS, Director, Weatherall Institute of Molecular Medicine, University of Oxford, John Radcliffe Hospital, Headington , Oxford. OX3 9DS (UK) under ICMR International fellowship for Indian Senior Biomedical Scientist 2015-2016.(Period of two weeks: 17th November 2016 to 1st December 2016)</li>\r\n	<li>Visited Laboratory of Prof. Hideo Harigae, Department of Hematology and Rheumatology, Tohoku University Graduate School of Medicine, Sendai, Japan Under Indo-Japan Project of DST New Delhi ( period: 21st March 2017- to 29 th March 2017)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<p><strong>Recent Publications:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Roshan B. Colah, M.Sc.,Ph.D.,<strong>Prabhakar S. Kedar, Ph D. :</strong> Red Cell Enzymopathies in India <strong>In Current Update in Hematology -2006 pages19-30. (Book)</strong> .</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Prabhakar S. Kedar, Ph D. (Contributor):</strong> Laboratory Manual for Screening , diagnosis and Molecular Analysis of Hemoglobinopathies and Red cell Enzymopathies Edited By Dr Mohanty and Dr Roshan Colah, Balani Publishing House Mumbai India 2007 <strong>(Book)</strong> .</li>\r\n	<li>R. Colah, R. Surve, M. Wadia, <strong>P.S. Kedar</strong>, S. Phanasgoankar, A. Nadkarni, A.C. Gorakshakar &amp; D. Mohanty: Merits &amp; Limitations of Automated HPLC for Hemoglobinopathy Detection (Abstract). <strong>Indian Journal of Hematology &amp; Blood Transfusion</strong> 1999.vol.17:9 .</li>\r\n	<li><strong>P. S. Kedar</strong>, K Ghosh, R. B. Colah, D Mohanty. Chronic persistent haemolysis in an infant: can we affort to forget malaria as a cause? <strong>The Hematology Journal 2002; 3:114-5. (Now Heamatologica) (Impact Factor-6.53)</strong> .</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Prabhakar S